Whisk coconut milk, chia seeds, almond milk, and 1 tablespoon maple syrup together in a bowl for 1 to 2 minutes. Cover with plastic wrap. Chill until thickened, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour. Combine remaining 1 tablespoon maple syrup and mangoes in a food processor or blender; puree until smooth. Spoon coconut milk mixture into serving glasses. Top with pureed mango.